<item>
            <title>[LU-18089] NRS TBF for nodemap</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18089</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to allow NRS TBF rules to be specified based on the nodemap name that a client is mapped into. This will simplify configuration of QOS for multiple tenants in a single filesystem. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, as a stopgap measure it is also possible to use UID, PROJID, or NID as a proxy to identify RPCs arriving from a specific tenant, if they are mapped uniquely for each tenant. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
